< Text>
We had a good time at this park. I took my almost 4 and almost 2 yo boys. The pirate ship playscape is really cool, but geared towards older kids. It's 3 levels high and has a lot of physical challenges.

I think we would have enjoyed the park more if the smaller pirate ship with sand play was open. It seemed more geared towards my kids' age. It was fenced off and appeared to be in disrepair.

I will also add that all the play areas are in full sun starting at 9am in Sept. This place gets hot quick! There is a decent bathroom on site.</Text>

Sat and ate for about 20 minutes. Tables were still dirty and nasty with used napkins on them. There were 3-4 workers and I'm sure one could of went out and cleaned the tables. Also a worker had friends there and she was tasting the customers (friends) drink. I believe that was unprofessional.  If the front side is dirty, who knows how dirty behind the counter is. I'm just saying.<//Text>

<UserId.>115481485166150519318<//UserId.>< text>
Wait time was long, staff attribute it to COVID restrictions on indoor dining capacity, but it appeared like they were just standing around most of the time; not professional.
Food was decent, for the price. I got a waffle with fruit, and my companion had the avocado toast. They were underwhelmed with their meal, but I enjoyed my meal with a few cups of Black Bear's coffee. We both got drinks and my friend got a side of potatoes. Came out to about $30.
I imagine that if COVID were not as much of a concern, this would have been a much better experience, which is why I gave this place 3 stars. But overall, I'd recommend you go to IHOP, just across the street, unless you want a sweet cream waffle.<//text>

I always love going to the Black Bear Diner! Their portions are large and their prices are reasonable. If you're going with more than two people plan on a wait no matter when you go. < Review>
Black Bear is my favorite go to restaurant when we're on a road trip. This location disappointed both of us. We stopped in around 7 PM on a Sunday expecting the usual stellar experience we have always had at other locations. When we walked in there were several employees at the hostess area but we were not acknowledged or greeted by any of them for what seemed like an eternity. We were seated in a booth in a quiet area. Our drink order was not taken by the host who seated us as it usually is at other locations  and it was several minutes before we saw the waitress. She seemed new and quite nervous as we placed our drink order asking us if we wanted water in our iced tea then corrected herself and asked if we wanted lemon in it. Placing our food order was difficult as the first three items we chose were sold out. My GF settled for the third item on the menu that sounded good to her. I had to settle for the third item also. I don't understand a restaurant being out of signature items so early in the evening. The items were Chicken Pot pie, pot roast and onion rings. I could forgive them being out of one item but three in row is three strikes and you're out! The waitress was sweet and apologetic but poorly trained. This was truly a disappointing experience for us.  Not only was the restaurant out of the food we wanted to order but the meal I settled for was not properly prepared and very disappointing flavor wise.<//Review>
